        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Hatley Park National Historic Site</h2>
        <p>On the western outskirts of Victoria you'll find the <strong>Hatley Park National Historic Site</strong>, which hosts the lovely Hatley Castle. Surrounding this stunning 20th century mansion are woodland parks, in addition to beautiful formal Edwardian gardens.</p>
        <p>Hatley Park also has a fascinating history. At the outbreak of WWII the castle was purchased by the British Royal Family, who planned to relocate to it during the war in order to stay safe, however they ended up staying in London.</p>
        <p>Hatley Castle is also extremely well-known as the filming location for Xavier's School for Gifted Youngsters, featured in nearly every X-Men and Deadpool film since X2: X-Men United. Additionally, the castle has been featured in many other films and TV shows.</p>
    </section>


